    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Textile weaving technique in which a pattern is formed or the ground enriched by the use of more than one series of weft strands; the patterning is done using either a supplementary or complementary weft.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000043641/Burnham, Warp and Weft (1980)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Técnica de tejido de textiles en la cual se forma un diseño o en la cual el fondo es enriquecido utilizando más de una sola serie de hebras de trama. El diseño se realiza utilizando una trama ya sea suplementaria o complementaria.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Weeftechniek waarbij een patroon wordt gevormd of de ondergrond wordt verrijkt door gebruik van meer dan een serie scheringdraden; het patroon wordt aangebracht met extra of aanvullende inslag.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099095/Diehl, e.a, Textiellexicon (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>使用一組以上的緯線線股，形成圖案或裝飾底布的紡織品編織技術；以增補或補充用緯線構成圖案。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
